<br>
If I understand Sanya correctly, she is suggesting that the attacker's skill level will be checked against the target's armor type.  This could boil down to your 30th level Armsman, who is fully specced in Slash and has +4 from items, realm rank, etc., fighting a Studded Leather wearing tank.  <br>
<br>
34th vs. 17% Absorption.  A level 5 will probably only be something like a 5th or 6th vs. 17% absorption.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Perhaps I am an optimist, but this change may encourage those under 45th to engage in more open RvR.  While I found the 30—35th Battle Grounds to have been an absolute blast, I was discouraged to learn that there was precious little RvR that I could take part in from the 36th through about the 45th level.  Grinding about 10 or so levels just to be able do engage in more RvR was discouraging, to say the least, the framerate loss of Emain Macha notwithstanding.  <br>
<br>
I feel that Mythic is taking some very positive steps to help smooth out the wrinkles in RvR.  While I feel that they are doing their best to improve the game, I do think that many of these &quot;changes&quot; should have been anticipated during Beta.  I know that on-line games need to be able to change with the ebb and flow of the game; yet many feel that DAoC was released about six months too early.  <br>
<br>
Be that as it may, I am looking forward to 1.52.  <br>
