I am concerned that the removal of the lvl based to hit modifier may give players with buff bots or friends who buff them through the roof an unfair advantage.     <br>
<br>
When I get full base and spec line buffs from a good enhance cleric my stats go through the roof.  My weapon skill goes up over 100 points and my AF and HP skyrocket as well.  I would probably need to ding 5 or more lvls to get that kind of a stat improvement without buffs.  <br>
<br>
However, as it stands now, even though my buffed stats make me &quot;look&quot; 5 lvls higher, I dont fight like I am 5 lvls higher.  I can't go running around killing enemies or mobs that are 5 lvls higher than me as if they were yellow cons.  <br>
<br>
Similarly, even though buffs make a fight with an even con easier, its no where near as easy as fighting that same enemy or mob will be 5 lvls from now.  <br>
<br>
My guess is that the lvl based modifiers limit how much of an improvement over the &quot;norm&quot; for your lvl buffs will allow you to go.  At best, buffs make me &quot;feel&quot; one or two lvls higher.<br>
<br>
However, if you remove these modifiers then pretty much the only advantage an unbuffed lvl 45 has against an uber buffed lvl 40 is that his dps cap is 1.5 dps higher (.3 per lvl).  In fact if the lvl 40 has a 100% quest or player made and the lvl 45 has an 89% dropped weapon, their effective dps should be about the same.<br>
<br>
Right now if I spot an even con enemy the chance that he has full buffs is a concern, but a limited one.  If I spot a blue or green enemy, buffs are no concern at all.  <br>
<br>
I am worried that with this change, I may get creamed by a yellow if he's buffed and maybe even lose badly to a blue.  <br>
<br>
